15 WHEREAS, his entrepreneurial vision also encompasses U2 Salt Ltd., a 600-acre salt mining
16 and refinery operation in Winneba, Central Region, demonstrating his commitment to
17 industrial diversification and Ghana's economic development; and
18 WHEREAS, in recognition of his enduring impact, Dr. Sarpong was awarded an honorary
19 Doctorate Degree of Philosophy in Law from Barkley University and was named an
20 Honorary Ambassador of Business Entrepreneur in West Africa by the Peristrofi World
21 Honorary International Award Conference; and
22 WHEREAS, throughout his career, Dr. Sarpong has earned numerous accolades and
23 appointments, inspiring aspiring entrepreneurs and strengthening communities across
24 generations through his steadfast dedication and visionary leadership; and
25 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable individual be
26 appropriately honored during this special time.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
28 the members of this body recognize and commend Dr. Ernest Ofori Sarpong for his
29 outstanding contributions to entrepreneurship, philanthropy, and national development as
30 well as extend sincere best wishes for continued success.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
32 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Dr.
33 Ernest Ofori Sarpong.
